1.title: The Aftermath
1.plot: When Ruby,Damien and Julian come to find out the news that they didn't make the audition. Leaves the trio to discuss many important issues leading to that crazy experience. The gang, starts to uncover some deep secrets between Ruby's relationship with Cynthia. Plus,Damien begins to get lucky in the love department.

2.title: Simply Sassy
2.plot: When Cynthia tells Ruby on the importance of auditioning for "Simply Sassy," things take a left turn when the School Leading Dance Group Captain Christian, takes an interest in Ruby.

3.title: Guess Who I Bumped Into at the Movies
3.plot: When Ruby goes on a date with Christian at the Movie Theatre's,things get messy When Cynthia's Gossip Girl Muffin Macdeou catches them together.

4.title: Damien Gets Lucky
4.plot: While on a 3-way phone call between Julian,Damien and Ruby. Damien informs the trio on his excitement on going on his first date with the guy at the Restaurant. Plus, Ruby begins to patch things up with Cynthia and squash the beef between there turmoil.

5.title: He Told You... WHAT?
5.plot: When both Damien and Brian wake up the next morning, they realize, they just ended up sleeping together. Which in the end, makes Damien try to figure out if he had any sexual relations with Brian. Plus, Julian struggles to accept the fact while telling everyone he's teaching a class for a dance workshop, he comes to find out not one person cared to show support.

1.title: Julian's Big News
1.plot: When Julian tells Ruby and Damien about a Cruise Line Audition the gang gets excited on this big opportunity. But,problems arise when they come to find out it a group audition.

2.title: Your Over Rehearsing Us!
2.plot: Julian Teaches Ruby and Damien the Choreography but the amount of times re-doing due to Julian demand of control makes Ruby and Damien Exhausted.

3.title: The Audition
3.plot: Julian,Damien and Ruby get ready for there big Cruise Line Audition. But when they find out the Audition it not what it seem to be they start to panic

imdb.plot outline: When Julian discovers an open casting call audition for a Cruise line. He immediately tell's his 3 Dancer friends Damien and Ruby on the importance of auditioning as a trio and coming up with a collaborative dance piece. Difficulties strike when all 3 friends start to underestimate them selves on working together when personalities clash. Will Julian,Ruby and Damien can put aside there differences and work out as a team to astound the judges. Or will there competitive streak will get the best of their passion and the love for each other.
